Sentencas: Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.5Fe0.5O3-delta (SYTF0.5) is investigated as an alternative anode in H-2 fuels containing H2S (0-200 ppm).
Titulo: Sulfur Tolerance Effects on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.5Fe0.5O3-δ as an Alternative Anode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Although additional ionic conductivity is introduced by aliovalent substitution of Ti4+ by Fe3+ in the B-site, the SYTF0.5 has lower electrical conductivity than that of the Sr0.92Y0.08TiO3-delta.
Titulo: Sulfur Tolerance Effects on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.5Fe0.5O3-δ as an Alternative Anode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Due to the mixed ionic and electronic conductive (MIEC) property exhibited in the SYTF0.5 anode, the electrochemical performance of the SYTF0.5 anode is improved, as well as the sulfur tolerance.
Titulo: Sulfur Tolerance Effects on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.5Fe0.5O3-δ as an Alternative Anode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities in H-2 at 900 degrees C for the SYT anode and the SYTF0.5 anode were 56.9 and 98.6 mW/cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Sulfur Tolerance Effects on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.5Fe0.5O3-δ as an Alternative Anode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density in the SYTF0.5 anode at 200 ppm of H2S concentration decreased by only 12.9% (86.3 to 75.2 mW/cm(2)).
Titulo: Sulfur Tolerance Effects on Sr0.92Y0.08Ti0.5Fe0.5O3-δ as an Alternative Anode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
